ACT:
 Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898, s. 429-Difference of opinion between two judges of High Court-Reference to third judge-Third judge can deal with whole case and entertain new plea.
 Prevention of Corruption Act, 1947, s. 5A and Code of Criminal Procedure, s. 12-Jurisdiction of Magistrate under s. 5A does not extend to whole of India-Magistrate can exercise jurisdiction under s. 5A throughout district in which he holds charge but not outside district.
 
